					<H2>Identifying the Problem</H2>
					<p align="justify">Each year, scientists at pharmeceutical companies race to develop vaccines to address the ever-evolving influenza A. While these vaccines are effective most of the time, there are some years where influenza A is one step ahead of the vaccine, resulting in increased influenza-related fatalities. This occurs because the vaccine is a retroactive treatment; Scientists develop vaccines based on observations made from previous years.</p>

					<p align="justify">Another issue that pharmeceutical companies struggle with annualy is predicting the quantity of vaccines they should produce. Since the government requires that vaccine distributors report their vaccine quota before they begin producing, pharmeceutical companies have to predict how much demand there will be for the vaccine. </p>
